view.name: Oregon Library Directory
view.description: This data contains basic contact and location information on public, academic, special, tribal, and volunteer libraries in Oregon. Data maintained by the State Library of Oregon and updated quarterly.

columns.name: LIBID
columns.description: Unique identifier for the library entity.

columns.name: Library Name
columns.description: The legal name of the library.

columns.name: Alt/Branch Library Name
columns.description: An alternate name for the library, a colloquial name it may be known by, or the name of a specific branch of a larger library system.

top.item: Institute of Marine Biology Library/Loyd and Dorothy Rippey Library

columns.name: Library Type
columns.description: A category for the library that best describes the community served.

columns.name: Location Type
columns.description: A category for the library location that describes the relationship between the outlet location and its parent library.

columns.name: County
columns.description: The primary county in which the library is located.

columns.name: Physical Address
columns.description: The street address of the physical library location.

columns.name: Physical City
columns.description: The city of the physical library location.

columns.name: Physical State
columns.description: The state of the physical library location.

columns.name: Physical Zip
columns.description: The ZIP code of the physical library location.

columns.name: Mailing Street
columns.description: The street or post office box where the library location receives mail.

columns.name: Mailing City
columns.description: The city where the library location receives mail.

columns.name: Mailing State
columns.description: The state where the library location receives mail.

columns.name: Mailing Zip
columns.description: The ZIP code where the library location receives mail.

columns.name: Phone
columns.description: The general contact telephone number for the library location.

columns.name: Email
columns.description: The general contact email address for the library location.

columns.name: Website
columns.description: The general website URL for the library location.

columns.name: Resource Network
columns.description: The library consortium with which the library location shares materials. This attribute is only included for Main library locations.

columns.name: Population Served
columns.description: An estimate of the number of people served within the library's greographic area or parent institution. For academic libraries, this number if their student Full-time equivalent count.

columns.name: Geocoded Address
columns.description: Point-based latitude & longitude coordinates for library, imputed by platform based on Physical address fields.

columns.name: 2010 House Districts
columns.description: This column was automatically created in order to record in what polygon from the dataset '2010 House Districts' (7u8j-y3re) the point in column 'geocodedaddress' is located.  This enables the creation of region maps (choropleths) in the visualization canvas and data lens.

columns.name: 2010 Senate Districts
columns.description: This column was automatically created in order to record in what polygon from the dataset '2010 Senate Districts' (ciix-jbrk) the point in column 'geocodedaddress' is located.  This enables the creation of region maps (choropleths) in the visualization canvas and data lens.

columns.name: Counties
columns.description: This column was automatically created in order to record in what polygon from the dataset 'Counties' (i25a-xk5b) the point in column 'geocodedaddress' is located.  This enables the creation of region maps (choropleths) in the visualization canvas and data lens.
